[normal]Conclusion
[normal]AR5 does not 
[normal]address the reliability of climate models, because there is an institutionalized rejection of models whose definition lies outside of the prevailing emissions based climate theory. 
[normal]It may be the case
[normal] 
[normal]that grant funding bodies a
[normal]re reluctant to finance research that may undermine the general emissions policy. 
[normal]The climate research institutions, upon whom we rely for an honest and accurate provision of information, are quickly becoming the least reliable authorities at providing th
[normal]at same information, since it is their ambition to adhere to the 
[normal]aspirations of the IPCC, despite their 
[normal]100% failure record
