[normal]Since NASA’s Godard Institute for Space Studies (GISS) is an American organisation, whenever possible the USA is placed in th
[normal]e centre of the picture, to please both their tax payers and to provide a simple geographical reference. In this particular image a large slice of West Africa and South America can be seen, but no USA. To produce the same image with the US
[normal]A
[normal] in the picture,
[normal] one would be confronted with the fact that the sea warming 
[normal]zone
[normal] as shown here
